title: Child rapper dies aged 14 as family say brother has also passed away
description: A child rapper has died suddenly aged 14 as her family spoke of its "unbearable loss" - revealing her brother had also passed away.

title: Robbie Robertson, lead guitarist and songwriter of The Band, dies
description: Robbie Robertson, lead guitarist and songwriter of The Band, has died aged 80.

title: Syria's President Assad would 'welcome home refugees'
description: Syrian President Bashar al Assad has said he would welcome home refugees who escaped the country's long-running civil war.

title: At least six dead after wildfires destroy large parts of town on Hawaiian island
description: At least six people have died after wildfires rampaged through parts of the Hawaiian island of Maui, officials have said.

title: Singer from Oscar-winning Searching for Sugar Man documentary dies
description: Singer-songwriter Sixto Rodriguez, who became the subject of the Oscar-winning documentary Searching for Sugar Man, has died aged 81.

title: British doctor among five people shot dead in South Africa unrest
description: A British man is among five people who have been shot dead in protests in South Africa.

title: Ousted Niger president 'low on food' two weeks after military coup
description: Niger's deposed president is running out of food and facing other increasingly dire conditions two weeks after he was ousted in a military coup and put under house arrest, an adviser has said.

title: Amazon nations fail to agree on deforestation goal as they call on industrialised countries to do more
description: Eight Amazon nations have failed to agree on a common goal for ending deforestation in a two-day summit in Brazil, as they urged industrialised countries to do more to preserve the rainforest.

title: Mic hurled by Cardi B at fan sells for almost $100,000 on eBay
description: A microphone hurled by Cardi B at an audience member in Las Vegas has been sold for almost $100,000 on eBay.

title: Imran Khan's plea for suspension of conviction is rejected
description: A Pakistani high court has turned down an appeal by jailed former prime minister Imran Khan to suspend his conviction on corruption charges, as the country's parliament is set to be dissolved.

title: Russia to build up forces at western borders 'in response to NATO threat'
description: Russia is planning to build up its forces at its western borders following Finland's accession to NATO, the country's defence minister Sergei Shoigu has said.

title: At least 33 killed in Beijing after devastating flooding in northern China
description: The death toll from devastating floods in China's capital Beijing has now risen to 33, according to officials.

title: More complaints about Lizzo's behaviour being investigated in wake of lawsuit
description: More complaints into Lizzo's behaviour are being investigated by lawyers representing her accusers.

title: Cousin of Uvalde school gunman arrested 'on suspicion of planning similar attack'
description: The cousin of the teenager responsible for the deadly primary school shooting in Uvalde, Texas has been arrested after his family tipped off police that he was planning a similar attack.

title: Eleven missing after fire at holiday home for disabled people in France
description: Eleven people are missing after a fire broke out at a holiday home for disabled people in eastern France.

title: Nine bodies found after fire at holiday home for disabled people in France
description: The bodies of nine people have been found and two others are feared dead after a fire at a holiday home for disabled people in eastern France.

title: 'Dozens' of migrants killed in shipwreck off Italian coast
description: Forty-one migrants have been killed in a shipwreck off the island of Lampedusa in Italy, according to  local media reports.

title: Fears over deflation in China as prices plummet
description: China's annual inflation rate has dropped to -0.3%, heightening fears the country's sluggish recovery from COVID could have a wider impact on the global economy.

title: US lottery player wins historic $1.58bn jackpot
description: Someone in Florida has won a $1.58 billion Mega Millions jackpot - the third-largest ever in US history.

title: 'Still a great distance to go' in Hollywood writers' dispute, says Seth Rogen
description: Seth Rogen says the film studios and streaming giants are unable to get on the same page because they "hate each other" as the Hollywood writers' strike enters its 100th day with no hint of an agreement.
